#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier compares observed vs Poisson-expected. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now; tooltip will show live share % once Ocean stats are reachable again."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier compares observed vs Poisson-expected. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now; tooltip will show live share % once Ocean stats are reachable again."

#. placeholder {0}: fmt(expected24h, 2)
#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier is the observed rate divided by the Poisson-derived expected rate: Ocean's current share of network hashrate is {shareStr}, so the expectation over 24h (~144 blocks on the network) is ~{0} blocks. The denominator extends with elapsed-since-last-block so the value decays continuously between finds; at the moment of each find it equals exactly count / expected_for_window. >1.00× means we found more than expected, <1.00× means fewer. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h - Poisson σ is large at this window."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 24h. The \"X.XX× expected\" multiplier is the observed rate divided by the Poisson-derived expected rate: Ocean's current share of network hashrate is {shareStr}, so the expectation over 24h (~144 blocks on the network) is ~{0} blocks. The denominator extends with elapsed-since-last-block so the value decays continuously between finds; at the moment of each find it equals exactly count / expected_for_window. >1.00× means we found more than expected, <1.00× means fewer. Same number the chart's right-axis pool-luck line plots. Wide variance is normal at 24h - Poisson σ is large at this window."

#. placeholder {0}: fmt(expected30d, 0)
#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 30d. At Ocean's current share of {shareStr}, the 30d expectation is ~{0} blocks. 30d smooths almost all Poisson variance - a sustained deviation here points to a real share change."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 30d. At Ocean's current share of {shareStr}, the 30d expectation is ~{0} blocks. 30d smooths almost all Poisson variance - a sustained deviation here points to a real share change."

#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 30d. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 30d. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now."

#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 7d, same observed-vs-Poisson-expected ratio as the 24h row. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now; tooltip will show live numbers once Ocean stats are reachable again."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 7d, same observed-vs-Poisson-expected ratio as the 24h row. Pool hashrate / network difficulty unavailable right now; tooltip will show live numbers once Ocean stats are reachable again."

#. placeholder {0}: fmt(expected7d, 1)
#: src/pages/Status.tsx
msgid "Blocks Ocean found in the last 7d. Same observed-vs-Poisson-expected ratio as the 24h row, with the window extended: at Ocean's current share of {shareStr}, the 7d expectation is ~{0} blocks. 7d smooths the short-term Poisson variance: a sustained <0.70× over a week suggests something structural (lower hashrate share than the estimator implies, or a real upstream issue at Ocean)."
msgstr "Blocks Ocean found in the last 7d. Same observed-vs-Poisson-expected ratio as the 24h row, with the window extended: at Ocean's current share of {shareStr}, the 7d expectation is ~{0} blocks. 7d smooths the short-term Poisson variance: a sustained <0.70× over a week suggests something structural (lower hashrate share than the estimator implies, or a real upstream issue at Ocean)."

