msgid "Braiins's own `state_estimate.avg_speed_ph` reading - their internal estimate of current matched hashrate. Reacts to a CREATE_BID / EDIT_SPEED within ~3 min. The orange \"delivered (Braiins)\" line on the Hashrate chart below plots a different signal: real billed PH/s derived from the consumed-sat counter (Δconsumed / (bid × Δt)). That counter signal is the truthful long-run billing record but takes longer to catch up to a capacity bump because matched shares have to accumulate. During a Datum outage the counter goes to zero correctly while this estimate holds elevated for minutes - that's why the chart uses the counter signal."
msgstr "Braiins's own `state_estimate.avg_speed_ph` reading - their internal estimate of current matched hashrate. Reacts to a CREATE_BID / EDIT_SPEED within ~3 min. The orange \"delivered (Braiins)\" line on the Hashrate chart below plots a different signal: real billed PH/s derived from the consumed-sat counter (Δconsumed / (bid × Δt)). That counter signal is the truthful long-run billing record but takes longer to catch up to a capacity bump because matched shares have to accumulate. During a Datum outage the counter goes to zero correctly while this estimate holds elevated for minutes - that's why the chart uses the counter signal."

